On Tuesday, there are two possibilities for the number of pieces of bamboo Perry eats: either $3\cdot14-1=41$ or $14+1=15$. Since these are equally likely, we add the expected number of pieces of bamboo he eats on Tuesday: $41+15 = 56$.

On Wednesday, there are two possibilities for the number of pieces of bamboo Perry eats: either $3\cdot56-1=165$ or $56+1=57$. Adding these possibilities together gives $165+57=222$.

