Let $X$ be the number of blocks placed successfully. We can find $P(X=k)$, the probability that $k$ blocks are placed successfully, using the following formula:

$$P(X=k) = P(X > k)P(X = k) = \frac{1}{(54 - k) \cdot 1} \cdot \frac{1}{(54 - (k+1))} = \frac{1}{(54-k)(53-k)}$$

The expected number of blocks placed successfully is the sum of the product of the number of blocks placed successfully and the probability that that many blocks are placed successfully:

\begin{align*}
E[X] &= \sum_{k=1}^{52} kP(X = k) \\\
&= \sum_{k=1}^{52} k \left( \frac{1}{(54-k)(53-k)} \right)\\\end{align*}

This can be really difficult to evaluate directly. To make it easier, we can use the following trick: $$P(X=k) + P(X=k+1) + \dots + P(X=52) = 1$$

\begin{align*}
&\Rightarrow E[X] = \sum_{k=1}^{52} k P(X=k) = \sum_{k=1}^{52} k \left( \frac{1}{(54-k)(53-k)} \right) \\ &= 1 - \sum_{k=1}^{52} \left( \frac{1}{(54-k)(53-k)} \right) + \sum_{k=2}^{52} \frac{1}{(54-(k-1))(53-(k-1))} \\ &= 1 - \frac{1}{54} + \frac{1}{53} + \frac{1}{52} - \frac{1}{51} + \dots + \frac{1}{1} \\ &= 53 - 1 + \frac{1}{1} = \boxed{54}.
\end{align*}

Answer: 54

